description: Stuart is at the local bank depositing his bag of change...when suddenly robbers of unusual caliber decide to make an illegal withdrawal! This issue it's up to The Possum to stop the 7 Mexican Midget Wrestlers!!
name: Mexican Smackdown

person_credits.name: Blair Kitchen
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Why did The Nurse come to Heavenside with The Doktor? Is he aware of her private agenda? He appears to have hired her for protection, but will she bring both the Heavenside police and the intelligence community down upon him? And with Sing slowly piecing together the real reasons for his return, would that be for the best? Warren Ellis' satirical-political science fiction novel continues! The issue is available with a regular cover by series artist Ivan Rodriguez, or wraparound cover by Raulo Caceres, and also a rare 1-in-15 Future Warning Sign cover!
name: Marg Bar Amrika

description: Frost is the subject of a viscous attack - and wait'll you see who the attacker is! The bold new direction continues, with an increased emphasis on character-driven action and suspense!
name: Meltdown

description: The reinvigorated series continues with a villain straight from the pages of DYNAMO 5! The Noble family is hot on the trail of the super- villain called Bonechill, because he’s the only person who can save Frost’s life!
name: Cold Front

description:
Superstar artist Gary Frank returns as the new world of Superman for 2008 and beyond begins in Part 1 of "Brainiac"! Decades ago, Krypton went to war with Brainiac, a cold and callous alien obsessed with the control of knowledge. Superman believes he's faced Brainiac before, but he's about to learn the truth behind his close encounters as he heads down the road to his greatest triumph...and greatest tragedy.

And check out what the newly returned Cat Grant brought with her from the West Coast.
name: Brainiac, Part 1 - First Contact

description:
Born in fire. Raised by monsters. Destined to destroy. On an alien planet shattered by war, no one is stronger than Skaar, the savage Son of Hulk. But as a Fillian warlord, an Imperial princess, and a mysterious Earthman spread chaos through the wastelands, will Skaar save the puny survivors -- or smash them? Another epic fever dream from Greg Pak, writer of "Planet Hulk" and World War Hulk" -- featuring the return of legendary Hulk artist Ron Garney!

Hulk was unaware he left behind his newly born son, believing him dead like the rest of his people leaves Sakaar and heads towards Earth for vengenge for the atrocities committed against him. But the child is truly the son of hulk. Though Skaar was just hours born when he was lost to the fighting he was able to stand and fight. For a month he roamed the planet facing and besting any beast that crossed his path. When, suddenly, a group of women and children fleeing the Barbarians seeking to kill the newborn and children are attacked by the insects. Skaar helps the children but ultimitly can save none of them.

Time passes and Skaar is now traveling with a group of the now nomatic tribe. He is called their ssavior the surviving son of their once fierce queen. But peace does not last, especially on Sakaar. The barbarians, led by the Axeman find the tribe and with their beasts terrible flames make quick work of Skaar. The remanding survivers are brought to camp for the celebration of his death as livestock. As the barbarians prepair their boiling pots for the slaves Skaar reamerges. Killing the guards and standing toe to toe with the Axeman.
name: Cradle Of Fire

description:
Overview

It's Web-Slinger vs. Wall-Crawler as artist extraordinaire Mike McKone (FF, The Exiles) joins writer Bob Gale to answer the question – who is “The Other Spider-Man?” It ain't comin' down to another clone saga is it? If so, send all complaints to 1994!
name: The Other Spider-Man

description: The first volume of The Justice Machine team.
name: The Justice Machine; Death by Decree

description: At the ends of the universe, Wonder Woman falls victim to the Black Horizon, risking the safety of her soul. To salvage her very existence, she must ally herself with the legendary Beowulf and another fearsome warrior from DC's past! But that's only half of Wonder Woman's troubles, as Tom "Nemesis" Tresser runs afoul of one of Diana's unexpected houseguests!
name: Ends Of The Earth, Chapter 2: The Edge Of Insanity
Countdown to Extinction, Part 2

description:
DC's new weekly series TRINITY explodes in an extra-sized debut issue featuring art by fan-favorite Mark Bagley (Ultimate Spider-Man) and Art Thibert with lead stories and dialogue by Kurt Busiek (SUPERMAN, ASTRO CITY)!

The lead feature explores the unusual bond — and importance — of DC's top three characters, Superman, Batman and Wonder Woman, as a mysterious dream links them together and may prophesy important changes in their trinity!

In Superman's Metropolis, strange planets and suns are growing over the city. Batman finds his city changed and ruled by Lord Gotham. Wonder Woman has some giant robots to battle.

In the back up story, John Stewart is on the trail of Konvikt and Graak. Looks like they might be too much for him to handle.
name: A Personal Best At Giant Robot Smashing;  It's Gonna Throw the Car

description: The sad, bloody saga of Jason Vorhees is well-chronicled, but one story element of his origin remains untold - that of his mother, Pamela Vorhees! As seen in the original instant classic film, Pamela was a woman unhinged by her son's death at Camp Crystal Lake but what of the woman before that tragic afternoon? And Jason's father Elias?
name: Volume #1

description: Pamela's bloody tale of horror continues on the drive toward Camp Crystal Lake. But as the story of her son Jason progresses, Pamela's young passenger begins to suspect that not all is right in the Vorhees family...does she have anything to fear from the kindly older woman?
name: Volume #2

description: Universes collide! The Justice League vs. the Authority. The Legion of Super-Heroes vs. Stormwatch. The Justice Society vs. Tranquility. When opposites meet, chaos reigns!
name: First Strike

description: Colonial America. Salem. For mankind's greatest sin against God, they were born - the Coven of Thirteen. Thirteen witches granted elemental powers, each one derived from an aspect of Christ's crucifixion. One man stands against them: Elias Hooke. A new hero in the tradition of Robert E. Howard's Solomon Kane or Clint Eastwood's The Man with No Name from the screenwriter of Celluar and The Fast and the Furious: Tokyo Drift!
name: Salem: Queen of Thorns #0

description: 'TRIANGLE,' Part Three-It is the veritable Calm before the Storm as secrets continue to be revealed about ALL of your favorite BEDLAM Agents! Big and The Merrow travel to the UK to get some answers as Choopie tries to cope with the unseen responsibilities of being a King! Also, The Mothmen tip to what went on back in the Bermuda Triangle, and they are NOT pleased...!
name: Triangle

description: The already controversial series continues from the red-hot zero issue! Elias Hooke, dark crusader against the forces of magic, learns the secrets of his own origin, and the revelations nearly consume him! A new hero in the tradition of Robert E. Howard's SOLOMON KANE and Clint Eastwood's The Man with No Name, from the screenwriter of WANTED and THE FAST AND THE FURIOUS: TOKYO DRIFT!
name: The Sins of the Father: Part 1

description: The controversial series continues! The Queen of Thorns has set her sights on Hooke and his accomplices and will not rest until he is captured—and forced to face the truth about who and what he is! A new hero in the tradition of Robert E. Howard's SOLOMON KANE and Clint Eastwood's The Man with No Name, from the screenwriter of WANTED and THE FAST AND THE FURIOUS: TOKYO DRIFT!
name: The Sins of the Father: Part 2

description:
Overview

Helena Bertinelli's vigilante attack on the shadowy cabal known as the Hand makes her a marked woman in Italy — just as a childhood mentor returns from the dead and inspires her to don the Huntress costume for the first time.
name: Part 3: Respect

description: Legendary artist Herb Trimpe (The Incredible Hulk) joins regular B.P.R.D. writer John Arcudi and Hellboy creator Mike Mignola for the first of four one-shots which pick up from the March-April B.P.R.D. feature on MySpace/Dark Horse Presents. These stories are set before the events of B.P.R.D.: The Black Flame, chronicling the Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense's fight against the frog monsters. As the frog cult spreads across America, Roger the Homunculus returns to the site of the B.P.R.D.'s first clash with the frog creatures--the ruins of Cavendish Hall, where Hellboy, Abe, and Liz first encountered both the frogs and Rasputin (Hellboy: Seed of Destruction)--to track down the final pieces of the puzzle of the Cavendish family.

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description:
1. The Girl Whom Time Forgot (Superman, Batman, Superman Jr., Batman Jr. / written by Bob Haney : reprinted in Superman/Batman: Saga of the Super Sons (2007))

2. The Sorcerer of the Sea! (Aquaman / written by George Kashdan : reprinted from Adventure Comics #245)

3. To Call a Deadman (Deadman, Challengers of the Unknown / written by Denny O'Neil : reprinted from: Challengers of the Unknown #74)
name: The Girl Whom Time Forgot ; The Soercerer of the Sea! ; To Call a Deadman

description:
1. The Super-Phantom of Smallville! (written by Frank Robbins)

2. Clark Kent (Superboy Legend / written by E. Nelson Bridwell)
A 1 page article about Clark.
name: The Super-Phantom of Smallville!

description:
1. Cover by Jack Kirby, Murphy Anderson and Neal Adams.
  2. "The Four-Armed Terror!" written and penciled by Jack Kirby and inked by Vince Colletta. Reprinted in Jimmy Olsen: Adventures by Jack Kirby and Jack Kirby's Fourth World Omnibus #1.
name: The Four-Armed Terror!

description: How did the Unbound manage to take over Nightmaster's beloved kingdom of Myrra? Can they survive against a population that's been converted to a cult of black magic?
name: A Virus of the Mind: Part Two of Black & White

description: Green Arrow and Black Canary follow the trail of Connor Hawke's missing body to the heart of the League of Assassins. Will Plastic Man be able to pull himself together in time to help? Who are these new members of the League of Assassins?
name: A League of Their Own, Part 1: Rubber and Glue

description: Through sorcery and subterfuge Dr. Doom has taken possession of Excalibur, the legendary blade that can cut through anything--including Iron Man! If Shellhead can’t stop him from joining the sword with its enchanted scabbard, Doom will become invulnerable as well as invincible, and nothing will be able to prevent his hidden agenda. Don’t miss this exciting tale of technology versus magic, which features the premiere appearance of Iron Man’s surprising mystical armor, as well as a final page that is, quite literally, an eye-opener!
name: Chapter 3, Knight Games

description:
What could be worse than being attacked by living trees? Maybe being confused as the worst serial killer in the world.

Poor Cassie, and things just got started.
name: BUMPed, Part 1 of 2

description: Justice Machine annual featuring the T.H.U.N.D.E.R. agents! Also the Elementals make their debut in a back-up story!
name: An Echo of T.H.U.N.D.E.R.; The Shape of Things to Come

description:
Overview

The Destine family is caught between the Cross-Time Excalibur and the Inhumans of another reality! While at home, Griffin's machinations harvest Destine DNA in a bid to live forever! And patriarch Adam Destine returns to where it all began--Yden.
The unforgettable conclusion to the ultimate game of survival between the DCU's villains! Who will live? Who will die? Will anybody make it home?
name: We Gotta Get Out Of This Planet

description:
Overview

The execution will be televised! Black Spectre’s ingenious plan to destroy Moon Knight enters its final phase. As the whole world watches on high-def TV, Moon Knight faces a no-win situation. He’s already the poster child for super hero recklessness, but after this, he’ll either be dead…or Public Enemy Number One.
name: God and Country, Conclusion

description:
Second miniseries from the Vertigo Pop! collection

Rocky Lamont, rock 'n' roll legend, has seen it all. Fame, fortune, armies of adoring groupies, mind-bending drugs. But now, after nearly forty years at the forefront of pop royalty, Rocky has turned sixty and his youth is gone. Or is it? A long-forgotten gift from an Eastern guru may hold the key to restoring Rocky's vigor, but at what unholy price? And what does all of this mean for a talentless young street-singer?
name: My Generation: Part 1

description: The latest VERTIGO POP! miniseries continues. Over-the-hill rock legend Rocky Lamont's plan to recapture his lost youth moves forward, leaving behind a trail of the lowest deceit imaginable. As the hapless would-be rock star Sean is brought into Rocky's glamorous world, his ambition blinds him to the fact that he is being prepared for a fate possibly worse than death. And the apple of Rocky's eye, his lovely daughter, Zoe, reveals a hidden dark side that could spell trouble for her unwitting daddy...
name: My Generation: Part 2

description:
In the second installment of the NO MAN'S LAND storyline, Batman and his allies continue their fight to save Gotham during its darkest hour. Taking on a new costume and persona as Batgirl, the Huntress joins forces with Barbara Gordon, the former Batgirl, while Nightwing, the former Robin, tries to help the city's remaining citizens in any way he can. But as Batman begins to realize that he is fighting a fight he can't win, he collapses into a state of despair from which he may never recover.

Originally published as Batman #565, Batman: Shadow of the Bat #85-87, Detective Comics #732-733, Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight #117 and 119, and Batman Chronicles #16.
name: Volume Two

description:
Batman, Robin, Nightwing, Commissioner Gordon, and the Huntress (back to her former guise), continue their war against the gangs and super villains who want to take control of the quake-ravaged Gotham. As Mr. Freeze, Poison Ivy, and Clayface each make their individual plays for power, Superman visits No Man's Land for the first time and the newest Batgirl makes her first appearance ever.

Originally published as Batman #565-569, Batman: Shadow of the Bat #88, Detective Comics #734-735, and Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight #120-121.
name: Volume Three

description:
The battle between Ikonn the Unlimited and the New Men, help by Ripclaw goes on. The victory is uncertain but finally, Ikonn totally absorbs Reign. Even when Ripclaw stuns him, the new men is missing. 
The Cyberforce's member explains that some spiritual disturbance brings him here and that he watches the beginning of the battle between Reign and Ikonn (previous issue).   
Now he  thinks that Reign is still alive. And he is right because Reign succeeds to telepathically contact their friend. Thanks to his indications, Exit is able to reach the strange dimension where the Ikonn’s prisoners are. A few time later, Reign, a lumberjack, a ape, a bear and a indian are released and Ikonn disappeared, leaving only a strange piece a metal.

But, even if Ikonn is defeated, the future is clouded for the New Men. Dash has his leg broken by Ikonn, Pastime decides to quit the team and the Brotherhood of Man always plans to kill them.
name: One Step Beyond

description: This new series from 360ep(360jam) apparently serves as a prequel to the video game series Advent Rising. Gideon and Ethan Wyeth are two teenagers newly arrived on the asteroid Artemus, where their engineer father is running mining operations for the United Resources Corporation. The comic follows the storylines of the two brothers as they adapt to their new lives in the Academy. Gideon is an awkward freshman seeking acceptance, while Ethan is a star ROTC cadet trying to establish his authority as the new head of the slacker squad.
name: New Kid on the Planet

description: Set several decades after the events in the popular Blood: The Last Vampire anime film, an amnesiac Saya Otonashi lives as a seemingly normal high school student with her adoptive family in Okinawa. Horrible nightmares are the only hints at the violent life she once led, but her past is about to catch up with her and awaken the merciless warrior within. Chiropterans - powerful shape-changing creatures who need and crave blood - threaten humanity once more, and a mysterious organization called the Red Shield needs Saya's deadly sword skills and mysterious powers to aid in the fight against these beasts. As her submerged abilities begin to reawaken and as she seeks to regain her memories, Chiropteran warriors are guided by a mysterious leader to threaten Saya and her loved ones.
name: Volume 1

description: Collecting stories from KAMANDI: LAST BOY ON EARTH #1, #10 and #29, written and illustrated by Jack Kirby
name: KAMANDI, THE LAST BOY ON EARTH 80-PAGE GIANT

volume.name: Countdown Special: KAMANDI: The Last Boy On Earth

description:
The Hobbit, or There and Back Again is the book by world-famous English writer J. R. R. Tolkien. It is considered a classic of twentieth century children's literature.

Cover artwork by Donato Giancola.
name: TPB

description:
Overview

Five stories from across the Marvel Universe, illuminating key elements of the SECRET INVASION!

Captain Marvel takes a stand!

Marvel Boy ( Noh-Varr) makes a choice!

Wonder Man and the Beast face off!

Abigail Brand, Agent of SWORD finds the foe!

And the Agents of Atlas enter the fight!

So, what happened? 5 stories by 5 different creators:

  • The long awaited reason why Captain Marvel attacked the Thunderbolts mountain? I don't know. Marv gave himself up to the Skrulls and said he wanted to rejoin the Invasion. Then, next second, he is after the Thunderbolts. The only thing that links this is when Marv was watching the Thunderbolts on TV and saying they are an abomination.
  • Agent Brand floats in space, and recounts her first time on S.W.O.R.D. and dealing with Skrulls. Then she bumps into a Skrull batle ship and she looks like she can get into a vent. Pretty Meh
  • Wonder Man now is trapped with Beast from the Shuttle, and they discuss their past friendship and mistrust because of their situation. Then they separate. Pretty Muh.
  • Noh-Varr in The Cube has the Warden doped up on nanobots in Noh-Varr 's spittle, so Warden can report to Maria Hill. All the prisoners are getting a docile making wavelength from a program rescued from MB's ship computer until the Skrull virus breaks the wave transmission and it all goes to hell. A Skrull is the cause and MB destroys him while MB goes about forming his army. Interesting development.
  • The Agents of Atlas story is the most stunning. The Skrulls captured Namora and dehydrate her like Namor, but Gorilla Man and M-11 rescue her, take the Skrull General captive, and Marvel Boy, Bob Grayson, dissects him, and beheads him, in preparation for the counter attack of the humans. The General is commenting the whole time and eventually realizes these Agents are doing the self same thing the Skrulls were doing. I could just shout. But this is the only story not cross-referenced to another issue in Secret Invasion.
name: Farewell; In Plain Sight; Seems Like Old Times; Master of the Cube; The Resistance

volume.name: Secret Invasion: Who Do You Trust?

description:
“River Run” continues: moving deeper into the worlds of Anna's book, Swamp Thing's loyalties are tested when he meets Abigail Arcane, an evil young woman who's come to live with her kindly Uncle Anton.

In the third story of River Run, The Bad Seed, Swamp Thing meets an alternate version of Abby Arcane, living on an Iowa farm with her uncle Anton Arcane, his wife Anna, and their son Joey. But, this world's version of Abby is nothing like the version Swamp Thing knows, and she has a few ugly surprises in store for her relatives.

Note: This chapter is inspired in the earth-3 concept from the pre-crisis multiverse.
name: The Bad Seed: Chapter Three of River Run

description:
Overview

An advanced Alien civilization has engineered a mind boggling secret headquarters in Snap City for Frank "Madman" Einstein and the surviving members of the Atomics Super Group. A celebratory party may be in the making, but something sinister is part of the new decor. Is it "curtains" for Frank and the gang?

Haunt your local comic shop this march and be the first in line to find out.
name: Become Like They Are!

Captain America vs The Aliens - 1 page Hostess Twinkies ad - inside front cover

Copyright 1979, by UAC-Geoffrey

name: Pink Drama

description:
Thor - Good Overcomes Evil! - 1 page Hostess Fruit Pies ad

1) The Pink Panther - Cloning Pink - 8 pages

2) The Pink Panther - Pink Painter - 7 pages

3) The Pink Panther - Pink Gun Bearer - 7 pages

Copyright 1979, by UAC-Geoffrey
name: Cloning Pink

description:
In the fourth installment of the No Man's Land saga, Batman and his allies continue their quest to bring justice back to Gotham. But as Batman, Nightwing and Batgirl try to defeat the warring gangs of the city and reclaim Gotham, Bane, the man who once broke Batman's back, returns with his own self-serving agenda. Now, battle weary and physically depleted, the Dark Knight must find the inner strength and mental toughness to face the one man to ever defeat him.

Originally published as Batman #571-572, Batman: Shadow of the Bat #92-93, Detective Comics #736, 738-739, Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight #125, and Batman Chronicles #18.
name: Volume Four

description:
Notes:

  • Part 1: "Fathers on Trial"
  • Part 2: "Unwelcome Allies"
  • Part 3: "The Weather Bomb"
  • Flash Grenade Arrow used.
  • Reprinted in: Superman/Batman: Saga of the Super Sons.
  • The jumbo jet that Superman and Batman save from destruction has the Blackhawk symbol on the tail wing.
  • This issue contains the Hostess Superhero Ad, Superman and Lois Lane in "The Spy".
name: Hero is a Dirty Name

description:
1. Reform School Rebel (written by Frank Robbins)

2. The Super-Robot (written by Otto Binder)

3. Superboy's Powers (Superboy Legend / written by E. Nelson Bridwell : reprinted from: Superboy #52)

4. Doctor Rocket (gag strip by Henry Boltinoff)
name: Reform School Rebel

description:
1. Cover by Jack Kirby, Murphy Anderson, Neal Adams and photographic background.
  2. "The Big Boom!!" written and penciled by Jack Kirby, heads of Superman and Jimmy Olsen by Murphy Anderson and inked by Vince Colletta. Reprinted in Jimmy Olsen: Adventures by Jack Kirby and Jack Kirby's Fourth World Omnibus #1. The Four-armed Monster tunnels his way toward Project Cadmus' atomic pile. Can Superman stop it in time? And what about the rest of its kind?
name: The Big Boom!!

description:
In the finest tradition of Rock Hudson, America's favorite vampire lady-killer is anything but. After decades of dodging certain questions, the Count comes face-to-face with crack entertainment reporter Bob Berger. In a career-spanning interview on the set of HOLLYWOOD NOW! no closet will be left unopened!

Will decades of meticulously crafted public image go up in flames?

This is our gay issue and we're very proud of it.
name: Dracula...Confidential

description: Where have the old Hollywood monsters gone? In the age of computer graphics and green screen, the answer ain't pretty. Having lost all of his money in a dot-com scheme, Frankenstein's Monster is content to drink the days away. When a chance at work drops in his lap, can he sober up long enough to cash in? Will the whole affair end in pitchforks and torches?
name: Andrea Silverman: Agent of Frankenstein's Monster

description: Now it's time for everyone favorite convention: BAR CON! Carl London, the Wolf-Man, barnstorms the Midwest comic-con scene with third-string aging sci-fi actors in tow. How can one help but party like a rock star at Kansas' PREMIER sports /hotel bar? Hard questions are asked: Does one drink "in character?" If you buy your B-actor idol a drink, MUST he read your fan fiction? At the end of the night, the Wolf-Man faces a foe even his drunken, wolf-y prowess may be unable to defeat!
name: Return of the Wolfman

description:
Overview

'BREAKS' A charity football game turns into a nightmare when quarterback Jack Magniconte inadvertently kills another player. Is he the newest human to manifest a superpower glyph? And more to the point, will Ken Connell-who himself manifested the 'Starbrand' glyph-and Izzy Randall-possessor of the 'Nightmask' glyph-reach Magniconte before he's killed in the government's efforts to stop a superhuman Armageddon? WARREN ELLIS and STEVE KURTH's brilliant re-imagining of the super hero continues.
name: Break

description:
In the final installment of the NO MAN'S LAND saga, Batman begins to see the light at the end of the tunnel as the United States government step in to restore Gotham City. But after months of physically fighting for his city, the Dark Knight might see all of his work go in vain as Lex Luthor plots to own Gotham. While working against this "hostile takeover" as Bruce Wayne, Batman learns that his greatest foe, the Joker, has returned. Now, at his physical and mental breaking point, Batman must simultaneously fights battles on two different fronts, will he succeed or will Gotham forever be know as No Man's Land?

Originally published as Batman #573-574, Batman: Shadow of the Bat #94, Detective Comics #740-741, Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight #126, and Batman: No Man's Land #0.
name: Volume Five

description: It’s all been building to this. After five long years, the best superhero comic book in the universe has reached its monumental FIFTIETH ISSUE! Invincible and Cecil Stedman face off and after this issue, nothing will ever be the same. Also in this issue, Science Dog returns in an all-new back-up story... and the ORIGIN OF CECIL STEDMAN!

name: Bust

description: After leading a rogue Defenders team into battle, Nighthawk comes face to face with Tony Stark and Henry Gyrich - and...well...they're not called the LAST Defenders for nothing! But can the Defenders get it in gear for one last battle as the mysterious Yandroth makes his move? And what roles do KRANG and the SON OF SATAN play in the Defenders ultimate chapter?
name: What Means Everything

description: Desperate to regain her powers of magick, Nyx seeks help among the Voudou community of New Orleans. But the price she has to pay proves too high. Only Spawn can save her from the evil she encounters. The problem is, the last time they met, Spawn swore to kill her if their paths ever crossed again. Poor Nyx. Out of the cauldron and into the fire.
name: Voodoo Child

description:
Overview

Alexander, Hannibal, Napoleon, Patton. What if the greatest military mind of our generation was born in strife, surrounded by violence and combat since birth? When the gauntlet is dropped, the question isn’t “How did 17-year-old Destiny Ajaye unite the gangs of South Central into a killer army and declare war on the LAPD?” No, the question is, “Can anyone stop her?”

From the minds of writers Marc Bernardin and Adam Freeman (The Highwaymen, Monster Attack Network) and innovative illustrator Afua Richardson (Half Dead), Genius is a book that will have readers talking for months to come.

Our regular creative team of writer John Layman and artist Fabiano Neves take a one-issue break this month as we present a special one-shot story written by Keith (Batman) Champagne and artist Noah (RED SONJA) Salonga as Xena and Gabriele square off against a Strange Visitor from another planet.
name: Strange Visitor

description: Groot is here! And so is…hey, wasn’t he sunk in Antarctica? One day on the job, and our cosmic protectors have already made themselves a major new enemy! But how does that connect to Adam Warlock’s mystical past? Could it really be the threat he’s spent years trying to deny? And exactly what or who have the Guardians discovered frozen & adrift in space? It can’t be...can it? If you’re curious, give GUARDIANS a go and find out why critics like ComicAddiction.com say “Dan Abnett and Andy Lanning are the unsung heroes of the writing staff at Marvel Comics.”
name: Legacy

description:
Writers Len Wein and Gerry Conway with the art by Dick Dillin & Dick Giordano bring this volume of classic stories that ties in with DC's Megaevent FINAL CRISIS


NOTES:
Reprints Detective Comics #274 and Justice League of America (vol. 1) #111, 166-168.

volume.name: DC Universe Special: Justice League of America

description:
Overview

 You only thought First Born was over! Coinciding with the release of the First Born collected edition, a pair of all-star creative teams joins forces for two tales that pick up very literally from the ashes of First Born, and set the stage for coming events in the Top Cow Universe in this oversized special. Witchblade scribe Ron Marz (Samurai: Heaven & Earth) and artist Ryan Sook (X-Factor) team for a Magdalena story, while The Darkness author Phil Hester (Superman Confidential) joins with Lee Moder (Red Sonja, Painkiller Jane) to introduce a powerful new villain. Add to that a painted sequence by original artist Stjepan Sejic (Witchblade), and this book is ideal for new fans jumping into Witchblade, The Darkness, or the rest of the Top Cow Universe.
name: Stragglers;  Armies of the Night;  Crisis of Faith

description:
Overview

In order to correct the past and save the future, Booster Gold faces a startling reality — someone from his past must live and someone must die! Can the greatest hero the world has never known do what must be done to save all of time? 
 
Summary 
 
Rip Hunter, Daniel Carter, and Rose Levin arrive back at the present after a quick trip in the time stream, to discover Rip's Lab a mess.  The time sphere Booster used to travel the tim e stream in, is destroyed.  Rip's blackboard has also changed.  Rip decides that to save the present the three need to correct Booster's future. 
Meanwhile in space on Brother Eye's station The Justice League International, and Superman battle the Time Stealers. 
Booster learns that his father, Jonar is being controlled by Mr Mind, and it's been Mr Mind behind everything the past year. 
Meanwhile Rip and Rose steal a time sphere for Brainiac 5 and return it to Boosters present. 
Booster defeats Mr Mind but Blue Beetle realizes the only way to save his friends is for him to go back in time and die at the hands of Max Lord.   
The last scen is Blue Beetle going back in time and Booster being engulfed by a white light.
name: Blue & Gold, Chapter 5: Mindgames

description: As Peter Parker and Normie Osborn try to learn the identity of the brand new May, Spider-Girl investigates Humanity First and battles a brand new super-foe.
name: Who's That Girl?

description:
Overview:

There will be blood. Gallons of it. Because Cyclops needs only one scalpel for a surgical strike mission and Logan’s the ideal man for the job. Tonight, Wolverine flies solo—dressed in black and operating off the grid. And when the night is through, there will be mountains of corpses, and no one to answer to. What could be better?

PLUS, this one-shot features a solo Warpath story, as he learns what it really means to go home again.
name: Ain't No Dog;  Hunters & Killers

description:
Random hook-ups, internal fighting, envy…what's going on with Nightwing, Starfire, Flash, Beast Boy, Raven, Donna and Red Arrow? Can this team get their act together before their mysterious foes reveal themselves?

Raven tells the others about Trigon's plans and that he seems to have another child. Starfire asks why he'd want to kill all the Titans. Raven tells them that there's magic in names. They've been the only ones to defeat him. Raven says that she was able to psychically pick up the names of three other brides Trigon had. They set out to find them.

Flash and Donna discover that the lady they're looking for has been dead for almost three years. They wonder why there's been no record of her death. Later Flash mentions how sad it is not having any contacts or family. He also throws in that Donna knows what that's like. They get into a fight about family. Flash says that being married and having kids is a lot of work. Donna says she'd give up anything to have her husband and son back. They continuing arguing until they are interupted by Cyborg.

Nightwing and Starfire visit the former home of the second bride. The neighbors have told them that she died about two years ago but they can't be certain whether or not she had a child (with Trigon). Starfire comments on the sadness of dying alone. She tells Dick that when she feels alone she thinks of him. Dick replies that he thinks of her when he's not alone. Next thing they know, costumes are off and they're rolling around of the floor.

Roy, Raven, and Beast Boy visit the husband of the third. She died about four years ago from a brain aneurysm. Raven is on edge and bluntly asks if she had any kids with him or anyone before. The husband starts to get offended but Raven just gets in his face. The woman had changed her name twice and there's no record of her death. Beast Boy pulls her out. Outside Raven insists that he must've been hiding something. Soon Raven and Beast Boy are trading insults and blows. Roy has no choice but to shoot Beast Boy, who is in the form fo a giant bear. He's about to shoot again when Nightwing stops him.

Donna comments on how they've all been acting out of character. They've been caught up in Envy, Lust, and Rage. Three of the Deadly Sins. A voice says it's one for each of them. Three of Trigon's children stand ready to take on the Titans.
name: Family Affair, Part 2: Sins of the Father

description: Batgirl tracks Catwoman and the notebook stolen from Commissioner Gordon to a posh nightclub — where costumes are optional!
name: The Cat and the Bat, Part Two

description: In 2006, comics legend Harvey Pekar brought his unsparing tales of ordinary life to Vertigo with an all-new run of AMERICAN SPLENDOR, the comic that, 30 years earlier, rose 'from the streets of Cleveland' and changed how we look at comics. Often imitated but never duplicated, Pekar proved that he still has the power to 'make mundane reality seem like the highest drama' (Entertainment Weekly) in his critically acclaimed Vertigo series. Now, Harvey Pekar is back with an all-new series of AMERICAN SPLENDOR, featuring his funniest, most poignant, somber and uplifting stories from the complex life of an ordinary man. Once again, the Vertigo AMERICAN SPLENDOR pairs Harvey with some of the most exciting, innovative artists currently in comics, including in this special premiere issue, David Lapham (YOUNG LIARS, Stray Bullets), Chris Weston (THE FILTH, Fantastic Four), Dean Haspiel (THE QUITTER, Brawl), Mike Hawthorne (THE UN-MEN, Queen and Country), John Lucas (THE EXTERMINATORS) and other luminaries from both the mainstream and indie worlds. In this issue, they join Harvey to chronicle his battles with stubborn sofas, short sighted magazine writers, treacherous front doorsteps and many more obstacles for Harvey to overcome in his pursuit of a fulfilling and meaningful existence.
name: I'm No Help!

description: "Run Riot," Part 2 of 3! The Flash battles to save the lives of everyone in Iron Heights as he takes on Gorilla Grodd! Meanwhile, Hunter Zolomon gets the brunt of one of Grodd's horrible attacks. And at the end of it all, Grodd...well, that would be telling!
name: Run Riot, Part Two: On The Run

description: The senses-shattering conclusion to the 3-part "Run Riot!" The Flash heads after Gorilla Grodd, entering the frightening new Gorilla City. Will Wally West's attitude and anger be enough to stop an army of the most brutal fighters in the world?
name: Dead or Alive

description: Iron Heights, the Keystone City penitentiary that houses most of its supervillains and rogues, has turned its inmates loose, and now the problems begin! The Top takes the Flash for a spin, and his new powers are revealed. Plus, The Flash and Hunter Zolomon's friendship reaches a bitter end.
name: Off-Balance

description: Peek-a-Boo, the disappearing villainess, returns to oversee the operation her father desperately needs. But she's a wanted fugitive now. Like it or not, The Flash must bring her to justice! Plus, a terrible occurs in the relationship between Linda and Wally, and Hunter Zolomon ignores Wally's warnings about the Cosmic Treadmill and time travel!
name: Helpless

description: "Blitz," Part 1 of 4, leading up to THE FLASH #200! Professor Zoom returns in a story that reveals the secrets behind his origin! But what is his strange goal? It's not what you would expect!
name: Rogue Profile: Zoom

description: The countdown to the landmark 200th issue continues in "Blitz" Part 2 of 4! The insane speedster known as Zoom attacks Wally, believing that The Flash can only be a better hero by experiencing ultimate sorrow. First on Zoom's hit list? The DCU's other speedsters: Jesse Quick, Jay Garrick and Impulse! No one is safe from Zoom's grip!
name: Blitz, Part Two: Rush

description: The Flash fights for his life as Zoom begins his war upon Keystone City! Will the Flash survive? Also, check out how Jay Garrick, the first speedster, responds to the crisis!
name: Blitz, Part Three: Into The Fast Lane

description: The conclusion of "Blitz" (Part 4 of 4) hits like a ton of bricks as The Flash faces his final confrontation with his opposite number, Zoom! If The Flash manages to stop Zoom, he will pay a terrible price. Only with the help of his friends from the past can Wally put his life back on track...but in a way you'll never anticipate! The biggest change in the life of Wally West since he first donned the Flash costume happens in this special, extra-sized anniversary issue!
name: Blitz, Conclusion: The Final Race

description:
A bold new beginning for The Scarlet Speedster, as new series artist Alberto Dose makes his debut! In the aftermath of the most horrific attack on The Flash ever, the Fastest Man Alive is nowhere to be found! As Keystone City becomes a breeding ground for lethal street races and rogues, a new type of Flash emerges, a new identity, one we can't say anything else about!

Street racers have taken over the streets of Keystone City, and the cops seem powerless to stop them. The only two who seem to care, Detective Jared Morillo and Detective Fred Chyre are busy trying to solve the murder of Adams Perkins, the Keystone City Police Department's Forensic Scientist, who was frozen to death in the middle of August.

Meanwhile, Wally West, who has no idea he is the Flash, is working the overnight shift as a mechanic for the K.C.P.D. He is enjoying the job and likes his boss, Wheeler, but hates the hours, and isn't sure about Reece, Wheeler's daughter who works in the shop too.

When Wally goes to lunch he meets a strange man named Len, who unknown to Wally is Captain Cold. The pair share a conversation, like they met for the first time, even though they have battled countless times. When Wally gets home, his wife Linda is leaving for school, and implies that there relationship is on the rocks due to the lost of their twins and the hours of Wally's job.

That night as Wally drives to work, he gets an accident, but time seems to freeze and he is able to get the people involved free from danger. Then time starts back up and an explosion launches Wally from the scene. When he wakes up , no one knows what he did. Wally thinks it was all a dream but a strange man give Wally a ring and says "its time to run again" and disappears into the crowd.
name: Ignition, Part One: Driven

description:
"Ignition" continues! The Fastest Man Alive struggles to protect his fellow officers as the true identity of their killer is revealed. The Flash wants to bring the murderer to justice, but so does a rogue outside the law! Plus, a visit from the new rogue profiler for the K.C.P.D. is anything but pleasant for Wally and his wife, Linda!

Wally West has forgotten he is The Flash, but the events of the night before have made him realizes he has some sort of super-speed. After testing the limits of what he can do, he heads back to work at the K.C.P.D garage, where Wheeler, his boss, tells him about the latest cop murdered by being frozen to death. Their conversation is interrupted by Detective Jared Morillo and Alexander Petrov, who get under Wally's skin by mentioning he isn't as good as his uncle Barry Allen.

Wally goes for a walk and some would be muggers try to mug him. Wally tries to use his super-speed, but it doesn't work at first and he gets beaten up. Then when the muggers attempt to shoot him the speed kicks in and Wally is able to catch the bullets. Wally thinks he has the upper hand but the shock waves of his super-speed shake the buildings around him and they crash down on him, pinning him underneath.
name: Ignition, Part Two: Shifting Gears

description:
As the Fastest Man Alive attempts to come to grips with his new identity, a new Rogue announces his presence in Keystone City. But what is his strange connection to The Flash? Plus, meet the new Keystone City Rogue Profiler and see what Captain Cold, Keystone's most wanted man, has been up to!

Wally West, who still doesn't know he is The Flash, digs himself out of the rumble of a fallen building that he accidentally destroyed, while having a uncontrollable burst of super-speed. He then finds the Flash costume that popped out of the ring a stranger gave him days ago. Wally also learns he can heal quickly, and after calling 911 runs off to his favorite dinner to clean his head, and think about what happened.

At the dinner, Wally bumps into Len, a strange man who seems to be at the dinner when ever Wally is there. Unbeknown to Wally, Len is really Captain Cold. Len and Wally talk about Wally and Linda's relationship, but when news that the KCPD has Captain Cold cornered, Len excused himself and Wally leaves soon after.

Seconds later at the warehouse the KCPD have, who they think is Captain Cold cornered, Wally arrives and runs inside. There Wally learns the man the KCPD have trapped is not Captain Cold, but a new villain calling himself Mr. Element. Mr. Element then uses a gun much like Captain Cold to freeze Wally.

Meanwhile in the KCPD garage that Wally works at the newest Rogue Profiler Doctor Ashley Zolomon comes looking for Wally West.
name: Ignition, Part Three: Crash & Burn

description:
"Ignition," Part 4 of 6. As the rash of police officers frozen to death continues, someone close to Wally West becomes the next target! Trying to come to grips with who and what he is, our hero goes on the hunt for Captain Cold - the most wanted man in Keystone City - hoping to stop him before another cop is put "on ice!"

Captain Cold finds the body of Wally West, who doesn't remember he is the real Flash, frozen in a block of ice. Wally is alive and Cold takes the body before the KCPD can stop him. Cold then takes Wally to the ice rink to thaw him out and talk to him. Cold tries to convince Wally that he is innocent in the freezing deaths of several cops. Wally believes him, but still tries to take him in for questioning. Cold escapes and Wally is left wondering whats going on.

Back at the KCPD headquarters, Wally meets with Doctor Ashley Zolomon who wants to apologize for what her husband did, but Wally doesn't want to hear it. Later that night Wally returns home to find the Batman waiting for him.
name: Ignition, Part Four: Cold Reality

description: "Ignition," Part 5 of 6, guest-starring the Batman! The Fastest Man Alive struggles to protect Keystone City's police officers as the true identity of their killer is revealed. The Flash wants to bring the murderer to justice, but so does a Rogue who operates outside of the law. Plus, a visit from the new Rogue Profiler for the K.C.P.D. is anything but pleasant for Wally West and his wife Linda.
name: Ignition, Part Five: Secrets

description: The shocking conclusion to the 6-part "Ignition!" Determined to put a stop to the cop killings, The Flash races through Keystone City for a final showdown with the unexpected culprit. Meanwhile, The Flash struggles with revealing his secret to those closest to him. Featuring a 7-page sequence by Howard Porter (JLA) and Livesay!
name: Ignition, Part 6: Up To Speed

description:
Overview

At the start of a new storyline, the New Exiles find themselves in a world that never moved past the age of empires! In a world where super heroes first appeared, oh, some 406 years ago, both politics and science have taken a dramatically different path, landing the Exiles right at the outbreak of war between the British and the French.

Meanwhile, one of the Exiles’ enemies has been gunning for Psylocke, but what will happen when he comes face to face with…Lady Mandarin?
name: The War Day, Part 1 of 4

description:
Overview

The Laughing Mask--behind bars! Secrets of the Black Widow--revealed! Dynamic Man kicks ass! The Blue Blade bombs out! And the truth behind the origin of underground secret agent Rockman!

Spoilers

The Laughing Mask is brought in to police custody. Even though it's been noted that he might need to be placed separate from the normal prison population, he is placed in a cell with other inmates.

Black Widow continues her nightly excursions to the Goth clubs. There is a young woman that is interested in her and looks up to her. She wants to know where she always disappears to at midnight. Black Widow says it'd be better if she didn't know where she went or what she did.

Phantom Reporter has a bit of writer's block. He contemplates putting on the old costume when he receives a phone call from Mastermind Excello. He tells Richard that now that he's secluded himself, he is starting to see the flow of time again. Something terrible is going to happen.

Dynamic Man continues his fight against evil. He easily takes out the "Men of Tomorrow" in their giant mechanical robots. A group of men want to buy him a drink to thank him. He finally agrees to let them. In the bar, one man pats his behind which angers him to no end.

Captain Wonder is out saving lives too but is not speaking to anyone. It's clear that he is still grieving.

Colonel Dexter gets a visit from a young woman who thinks that Rockman might be her grand-uncle, Daniel. Her grandmother told her he was trying to unionize the men in his mining town against the company that owned it all. The owner finally brought in some men to kill him. Winning the fight, the owner set off an explosion that accidentally killed everyone below. Daniel was exposed to some gas that made him invulnerable. When he dug his way out, he discovered that the entire town fell into a sinkhole. All were dead, including his wife and daughter. He would pound on the ground and claim that he could hear them calling him from below. The Colonel told her it wasn't Rockman when she showed him an old photograph. He later said it would be better for him this way rather than know that he would never see his wife and daughter again.

In the end, the Phantom Reporter decides to make a comeback.

Encountering new forms of terror, Jack Stanton is stranded in Silent Hill. Unable to save his girlfriend and facing the mysterious girl named Sara, whose thirst for vengeance is linked to Jack's criminal life.

This is the end of the road for Jack. Which will be his ultimate decision?

Penguin's tenuous hold over the City quickly slips away as Batman and Gotham's other protectors close in for the final act of this epic gang war. Will Penguin pay the ultimate price? Or will the Dark Knight show Gotham's underworld boss a rare moment of grace? No matter the outcome, it all comes to an explosive conclusion here!
name: Book Nine: The Day The Penguin Died

description: The Locke family plays houseguest to Sam Lesser, just in from the West Coast, and ready to kill them one at a time to get what he came for: the key that will set his master loose. Acclaimed suspense novelist and New York Times best-selling author Joe Hill (Heart-Shaped Box) continues his all-new story of dark fantasy and wonder, with Gabriel Rodriguez handling art and cover duties.
name: Welcome to Lovecraft, Chapter Five

description:
Notes:

  • Part 1: "To Sleep No More"
  • Part 2: "What Ghosts be These?"
  • Part 3: "The Snarl of Da-Chiri"
  • The fictional Asian country of Tong-Buk seen.
  • This issue contains the Hostess Superhero Ad, Shazam in "Minerva Menace!".
name: The Dream Bomb

description:
1. Your Death Will Destroy me! (Superboy, Ma and Pa Kent, Mrs. Lang / written by Frank Robbins)

2. Revolt of Ma Kent! (Superboy, Ma and Pa Kent, Police Chief Parker / written by Frank Robbins)

3. Krypto (Superboy Legend / written by E. Nelson Bridwell)

4. Smallville Mailsack (letters : includes a Mike Esposito bio)

5. Giants Come in Any Size!
name: Your Death Will Destroy Me!

description:
1. Cover by Jack Kirby, Murphy Anderson, Neal Adams and photographic background.
  2. "The Guardian Fights Again!!!" written and penciled by Jack Kirby, heads of Superman and Jimmy Olsen by Murphy Anderson and inked by Vince Colletta. Reprinted in Jimmy Olsen: Adventures by Jack Kirby and Jack Kirby's Fourth World Omnibus #1.

The Newsboy Legion is on quarantine in Cadmus labs, because they may have a flu. But they want action. Then they meet a Scrapper Trooper, who might just be able to help them out.

In Metropolis, Morgan Edge gets irritated at one of his employees (a Don Rickles-lookalike) , and decides to have him killed (!?). Well, that`s just one of the reasons. The other is, that he can`t meet Don Rickles (famous comedian at the time), because the consequences would be disastrous.

He also decides to get rid of Jimmy Olsen and Clark Kent, who have proved to be pests to his criminal businesses. He sends both of them to cover a UFO-story. Guardian goes with them.

Rickles is transported out of town, to the UFO. Our heroes arrive to the scene, and are attacked by brutish thugs. Rickles accidentally traps Kent inside the ship, and also manages to make it go all the way up to space! Oy!

Meanwhile, the Newsboys and Scrapper trooper get out of the labs.

The thugs batter and capture our heroes and take them away.

They are poisoned with Pyro granulate grains, that will make our heroes self com-bust in 24 hours! Oh boy, how will they get out of this pickle!?
name: The Guardian Fights Again!!!

2. Mystery Ship

description:
Johnny Storm vs her former love, Lyja, the Skrull Warrior. Trapped in the negative zone with Franklin and Val, Ben and Johnny will have to overcome the odds if the Fantastic Four will have any chance of survival

 Spoilers
